ics, we believe that we have the opportunity to revolutionize the existing global assets trading paradigm. By allowing assets to be efficiently transacted worldwide, we hope to give everyone an equal opportunity to buy and sell quality assets from around the world, bringing wealth and prosperity to the masses. We\u2019re a driven team of innovators and builders, solving novel problems in innovative ways using creative technology. This is your opportunity to get in early on a team with global vision and localized efforts. You\u2019re the expert and we want to give you the runway to be the best. If you have the drive and passion to build the future of asset circulation with us, we want to hear about it. About the ROLE: We are looking for a CFO to drive financial and strategic leadership across our scaling business. You will continue to build our Finance function to ensure we are developing a scalable approach to long-term planning. You will be an entrepreneurial leader and a mentor across Apifiny you are an important driver in bringing people together as we scale and grow. Key Responsibilities: Direct the company's strategic planning initiatives and help to build out strong practices around FP&A. Partner with all members of the senior management team and other company leadership on business strategy Build and mentor Finance and Accounting team through the implementation of systems, processes, internal controls and policies Demonstrate strong Financial stewardship. Direct resource allocation, monitor company expenditures and help review and negotiate customer and vendor agreements Oversee internal and external Financial Reporting. Work with external CPA firm on tax and compliance matters. Set accounting policy. Help drive effective board meetings as well as manage communications with the BOD and current and potential investors Implement processes, frameworks and systems that allow us to capture and utilize timely and accurate data across the business to make better decisions Provide support on various operational tasks including P&L and financial projections, pricing and valuation models and company presentations Requirements: Must have held the CFO role in a U.S. public company 10+ years of finance experience in a leadership position Previous experience in a startup company is preferred Experience with secondary market offering/capital raising at a public company TMT - Technology/Telecom/Fintech/Media industry experience preferred Entrepreneurial spirit and passion for building Excellent verbal and written communications skills Desire to work in a dynamic start-up, and be effective resolving ambiguities High intellectual capacity, particularly in an analytical and strategic context Leader that will own the full spectrum of finance responsibilities You constantly question the status quo and believe there is always a way we can continuously improve Prior experience leading fundraising diligence efforts, ideally at a growth stage company Strong technical analytical skills Flexible, operationally focused CFO. A capable leader that will be a strong partner to the executive team and an excellent mentor and coach to a growing Accounting and Finance team CPA & MBA a plus Job Type: Full-time Pay: $115,281.00 - $289,552.00 per year Benefits: 401(k) Dental Insurance Health Insurance Paid Time Off Experience: CFO: 10 years (Preferred) IPO: 8 years (Preferred) Roadshows: 8 years (Preferred) Public Company: 8 years (Preferred) Mergers and Acquisitions: 8 years (Preferred) Additional Compensation: Bonuses Work Location: Fully Remote Schedule: Monday to Friday Company's website: www.apifiny.com Work Remotely: Yes Show full job description Quick Apply Stay Connected Contact Us SimplyHired Blog Facebook Twitter LinkedIn YouTube Job Tools Local Jobs Salary Estimator Post Jobs Free Resume Builder Browse All Jobs All Salaries All Cities All Companies Guides Resumes Cover Letters Interviews Careers Take your job search wherever you go. United States 